# CODEOWNERS — require a second reviewer ONLY on the irreversible surfaces.
#
# Rationale: the web app is fully recoverable (Vercel instant rollback + git revert),
# so it needs no mandatory review — rollback is a sufficient safety net there.
# The pipeline and DB schema write PRODUCTION data and infra (Neon; cohort_percentiles,
# qal_records) — a bad change there is NOT undone by reverting a commit, so those get a
# second set of eyes.
#
# This only takes effect when the `main` branch ruleset has
# "Require review from Code Owners" enabled. With required approvals at 0, PRs that
# don't touch an owned path self-merge; PRs touching pipeline/ or db/ need a code owner.
#
# NOTE: a code owner cannot approve their own PR, so list BOTH principals below once
# Christian's handle is known — that makes these paths a *mutual* review rather than a
# hard block. Until then, pipeline/db changes require the other owner to exist.

/pipeline/   @ktulrich
/db/         @ktulrich

